Distribution. Described from the Flores Sea in southern Indonesian waters (
Hansen 1910
),
S. anomala
is also known from the Marshall Islands and the Philippines (
W.M. Tattersall 1951
), Palau (
Ii 1964
) and the Ryukyu Islands (
Fukuoka & Murano 1997
). A single male has previously been recorded from Australian waters. It was taken by the Great Barrier Reef Expedition at the Low Isles anchorage (
W.M. Tattersall 1936 a
).
